{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Create a CPI-adjusted Unmarried Childless Person Nil-rate Inheritance Tax band",
        "additional_details": "This should then continue to adjust annually upwards. Since 2007 married/CP couples can double up Inheritance Tax allowances (the survivor getting \u00a3650,000 not \u00a3325,000). Since 2020 married/CP couples with children get a further \u00a3350,000 in allowances taking them to \u00a31M. We think the CPI indexation of the nil-rate band was abandoned since 2009 BECAUSE married/CP people have enough allowance. We believe unmarried childless people were entitled to expect their own allowance to continue to be CPI-increased since 2009 but the Government has not addressed this and a fair uplift is long overdue.",
        "background": "We think the Government should give single (unmarried) childless individuals (as a category of taxpayer) the Inheritance Tax allowance they would each enjoy now, had \u00a3325,000, the nil-rate band amount set in 2009, continued to be CPI-adjusted upwards annually each year since 2009.",
